  "title": "Application Engineer (Medical Device)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li><strong>Well Established Company</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Basic $4000 to $5500 + AWS + VB</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Excellent Welfare and Benefits + Career progression</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Working location: Boon Lay | Singapore</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Monday to Friday (8:30am to 5:30pm)</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Mechanical Engineering | Medical Device</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Identify sales opportunities and develop new accounts through market research and trends</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Proactively follow-up on assigned sales leads generated at market specific trade shows or web</strong></li>\n  <li>Prepare and submit quotations / proposals / project schedule</li>\n  <li><strong>Ensure customer orders are tracked accordingly</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Manage and grow existing accounts to ensure continuous growt</strong>h</li>\n  <li>Expand market share with existing and new customers</li>\n  <li><strong>Enhance value-added selling approach</strong></li>\n  <li>Provide quality after-sales support services</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Bachelors’ Degree in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Prior experience in Engineering or Medical related field would be an added advantage</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Candidates are encouraged to apply this position via <strong>Apply Now</strong> button with the following information in the resume</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>• Work experiences and job responsibilities</p>\n<p>• Current and Expected salary</p>\n<p>• Reason for leaving</p>\n<p>• Date of availability</p>\n<p>• Education background</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>NG DIAUM YEE (R2198031)</p>\n<p>EA Recruitment Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 21C0492</p>",
